7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Children’s Code;
prohibiting certain actions by the Department of
8 Human Services in relation to adoptive and foster
parents; providing certain construction; providing
9 for codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-8-113 of Title 10A, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. The Department of Human Services shall not:
17 1. Require any current or prospective adoptive or foster parent
18 to affirm, accept, or support any government policy regarding sexual
19 orientation or gender identity that conflicts with the parent’s
20 sincerely held religious or moral beliefs as a condition for
21 eligibility to adopt or foster;
22 2. Deny a current or prospective adoptive or foster parent any
23 authorization necessary to be eligible to adopt or foster based, in
24 whole or in part, upon the parent’s sincerely held religious or
